HEADWORD: Bethlemite
<hw>Beth"lem*ite</hw>
<pr>(<?/)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>An inhabitant of
Bethlehem in Judea.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An insane person; a madman; a bedlamite.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>One of an extinct English order of monks.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bethought</ent>⟦br⟧
